 Düzen Tekkal, Journalist and filmmaker. She says: "Iraq is one of many countries where Christians are being persecuted. Which is why it's so important that Pope Francis is traveling to the region."    Alexander Görlach, author and theologian. He says: "A Papal visit to Iraq in times of corona is far from wise."   Amir Musawy, Iraqi journalist. He says: "The pope's meeting with Grand Ayatollah al-Sistani will be a turning point in the Christian-Muslim dialogue."